* pprof (built-in Go tool)
  → “snapshot” of the program

  * goroutine profile (part of pprof)
    → where goroutines are *currently stuck* (stack traces)

  * block profile (part of pprof)
    → where they *block* (channels, mutex)

* trace (separate Go tool)
  → “video” of execution: creation, blocking, scheduler

---

Common leak causes:

* send to channel without receiver
* read from channel that is never closed
* missing `context` cancel
* no timeout (HTTP, etc.)
* forgot `ticker.Stop()`

